Description: The Deployd JavaScript Framework by Deployd aims to be an API building tool that provides ready-made functionality. This framework is written in JavaScript.

The iCloudDocumentSync project by iRare Media integrates iCloud into iOS documents. With this framework, users are able to sync, upload, manage, and remove documents from iCloud. The idea is to simplify the process. Sam's project features drag and drop from iCloud framework, delegate methods, iOS sample app, and frequent updates. Developers are invited to contribute to his work.
This Diffbot Client by Diffbot supports Dart programming language interaction with Diffbot APIs.

The Materialize JavaScript Framework was created and designed by Google, Material Design is a design language that combines principles of design. Google's goal is to develop a system of design that allows for a unified user experience across all their products on any platform.

The Mezzanine CMS Django framework provides MVC architecture, ORM, tempting, caching, automatic admin interface, hierarchical page navigation, save in draft or preview, schedule publishing, drag-and-drop page ordering, WYSIWYG editing, in-line page editing, drag-and-drop HTML5 forms builder with CSV export, SEO friendly URLs and meta data, shopping card module, multiple integrations, and customization features for the Mezzanine API.

This is a PHP SDK for working with Docker's API. Docker offers an open platform for distributed app development. This PHP SDK is still under development, and does not yet support all features of the API. Installation via Composer is recommended. See the documentation for versioning information and info regarding the further development of the SDK.
The Kohana PHP Framework by Kohana is a web development framework that allows for the building of applications. The framework is written in PHP5.

The Sails framework is a web framework that allows developers to build custom, enterprise-grade Node.js apps. It aims to resemble the MVC architecture from frameworks like Ruby on Rails, but with support for the more modern, data-oriented style of web app development. This Framework is for Node.js.

The Play Java Framework by Play allows for a high-productivity Java web application framework that integrates the components and API for web application development. The framework is written in Java and is available in Scala.

Phalcon PHP Framework by Phalcon is an open source, full stack framework for PHP written as a C-extension, optimized for high performance. Phalcon is loosely coupled, allowing for objects as glue components based on the needs of an application.

Slim is a lightweight micro framework that developers can use to build web applications and RESTful APIs in PHP. Features include a router, a resource locator and DI container, template rendering with custom views and more.

The Sensu Ruby Framework by Sensu is an open source framework that aims to provide a monitoring framework. By providing an agent, message bus, & event processor, Sensu enables developers and operations teams to compose telemetry systems to meet business specifications.

The Flickr iOS framework by David Casserly has been created to access the Flickr API just like the currently used gallery pro iPad app. With this framework, users have two options to call methods: by string or by classes. It does not support Mac OS X. Available usage with API notes and authentication. Developers will be able to load interesting photos using the generated Flickr API model classes. This framework is written in Objective-C.

Cloudmade Geocoding is a system that provides predictive learning, map data enrichment, and navigation & guidance in connected cars. Cloudmade blog encourages users to work with a static framework available on developer's Landon Fuller site. This framework includes links, sections, and archives. This work was created to interact with iPhones.

The Cloudmade Geocoding API supports connected car content features such as map portals and driver analytics. This OS framework created by Apple can be useful for developers who want to build in Xcode to automate structures for Cloudmade according to their blog. Available directory, configuration, and compatibility.

PSX is a framework written in PHP to create RESTful APIs. It provides tools to handle routing, API versioning, data transformation, authentication, documentation and testing. With PSX, developers can build an REST API around an existing application or create a new one.

The Ensembles Core Data iOS Framework by Drew McCormack aims to extend Apple's Core Data framework to add peer-to-peer synchronization for Mac OS and iOS. Multiple SQLite persistent stores can be coupled together via a file synchronization platform like iCloud or Dropbox. The framework can be readily extended to support any service capable of moving files between devices, including custom servers. It is written in Objective-C.

The iOS Charts Framework by Daniel Cohen Gindideveloping is for both platforms, as the learning curve is singleton- it happens only once, and the code stays very similar so developers don't have to go around and re-invent the app to produce the same output with a different library. This framework is written in Objective-C.
The ROAD iOS Framework by EPam Systems is a set of reusable components taking advantage of extra dimension Attribute-Oriented Programming adds. This framework is written in Objective-C.
The CocoaLumberJack iOS Framework By CocoaLumberJack is a logging framework for Mac and iOS. Written in Objective-C.
The Mantle iOS Framework by Mantle is a model framework for Cocoa and Cocoa Touch. It is written in Objective-C.

The AFNetworking iOS Framework by AFNetworking is a networking library for iOS and Mac OS X. It's built on top of the Foundation URL Loading System, extending high-level networking abstractions built into Cocoa. It has a modular architecture with well-designed, feature-rich APIs. The framework is written in Objective-C.
The DFImage Manager by Alexander Grebenyuk is an iOS framework for loading, caching, processing, displaying and preheating images. The framework is written in Objective-C.
The UiImage iOS Framework by Mad Dog Software has IOS UIImage processing functions using the vDSP/Accellerate framework for speed. The framework is written in Objective-C.

The GPUImage framework is a BSD-licensed iOS library that allows developers to apply GPU-accelerated filters and other effects to images, live camera video, and movies. Further, GPUImage allows for writing custom filters, supports deployment to iOS 4.0, and has a simpler interface. This framework is written in Objective-C.

The WURFL is a Device Description Repository (DDR), or framework that enables applications to map HTTP requests to a description of the capability of the mobile device that requests the page. This framework is written in PHP,

This Go client is auto generated by Google for use with their APIs, including BigQuery. The BigQuery API harnesses Google's major processing power to quickly query append-only data tables with SQL-like commands. See the project documentation for details on installing the API and importing the Go client.
